Peoplefluent is a provider of Talent Management Systems headquartered in Waltham, Massachusetts. The company was formerly known as Peopleclick Authoria, and changed its name in June 2011.[1]. Industry Analyst Josh Bersin claims Peoplefluent's revenues are approximately $90 million.[2] The company was formed by merging Waltham, Massachusetts based Authoria with Raleigh, North Carolina-based Peopleclick in January 2010. Peopleclick was one of the largest employers in downtown Raleigh at the time of the merger according to the North Carolina newspaper News & Observer.[3] In addition to talent management systems, the company also produces software for vendor management and provides software and services for affirmative action plans. On May 1, 2012, Peoplefluent announced the acquisition of Socialtext.[4]
